                <head>278. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName> and Prime Minister
                        <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName>, accompanied by members of
                    their parties, were guests at a dinner on March 22 given by the Governor of
                    Bermuda, Sir <persName>John Woodall</persName>, at his residence. (Eisenhower
                    Library, President’s Appointment Book)</p>
